		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I also used Irfan Wiew to convert from more colors to 4 colors. It's better to first convert to grayscale mode, then convert to 4 colors step. Inserting it in a CHR file is doable, you don't need BMP2NES at all. I've used TileMolester to instert the new 4 color pitcure into NES format.
<br />Here you are an example :
<br />EDIT :
<br />From this image : <a href="http://jonathan.microclub.ch/cat/minetbougie.jpg" class="postlink">http://jonathan.microclub.ch/cat/minetbougie.jpg</a>, I was able to input it in a NES ROM, it uses MMC5 to do the high CHR adress selection <a href="http://jonathan.microclub.ch/cat/cat.nes" class="postlink">http://jonathan.microclub.ch/cat/cat.nes</a>

		

